content:
This warning:

StructureDefinition.where(url = 'http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-genderIdentity') warning The Implementation Guide contains no examples for this extension

even though this example: http://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/US-Core/Patient-example.html

has it:

#...extensions...
  - url: 'http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-birthsex'
    valueCode: F
  - url: 'http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/StructureDefinition/us-core-genderIdentity' #<<<<Here it is ???
    valueCodeableConcept:
      coding:
        - system: 'http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/v3-NullFlavor'
          code: ASKU
          display: asked but unknown
      text: asked but unknown
# rest of resource...

That warning is complaining about a lack of explicit examples, I think. I.e. examples that, at their root, are declared as examples of that profile. You can suppress if it's an example elsewhere - just indicate where
it is gone - thanks for follow up.
Eric Haas has marked this topic as resolved.
